                            <comment id="16848994" author="jking3" created="Mon, 27 May 2019 14:39:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks - marking this as a blocker for 0.13.0.  In the meantime you can download a 0.12.0 tgz from github off the 0.12.0 tag.  We really shouldn&apos;t have any links at all in the archive that I&apos;m aware of, so part of the packaging solution will be to guarantee none are present.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16897652" author="jking3" created="Thu, 1 Aug 2019 00:46:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is still open for 0.13.0 - will have to take a look at the distribution packages to see where they come from.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16935275" author="jensg" created="Sun, 22 Sep 2019 09:50:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jking3&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jking3&quot;&gt;jking3&lt;/a&gt;: Any chance we get that done in near time? If not, what other options do we have?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16935276" author="jensg" created="Sun, 22 Sep 2019 09:52:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=danieljewell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;danieljewell&quot;&gt;danieljewell&lt;/a&gt;: Do you have more details available? How can I check this? What is the exact error message you get?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried looking into the tarball but the tool I used did not reveal any links at all, let alone hardlinks. What I found was however a number of folders that are owned by &quot;root&quot;. Could that be the issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16945299" author="jensg" created="Sun, 6 Oct 2019 10:42:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=danieljewell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;danieljewell&quot;&gt;danieljewell&lt;/a&gt; could you please comment? Otherwise I am going to ignore the &quot;blocker for 0.13.0&quot; state.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
